Course Reflections

March 4th, 2025

Today we learned abour pre-rendering and real-time rendering. Real-time rendering makes your workflow more flexible because assets don't need to be pre-rendered. IRL implementation is happening slowly because it requires updated infrastructure and training, which is expensive. It's also somewhat less high-fidelity than pre-rendered assets, but the gap is getting smaller over time, and I can't tell the difference anyway lol
We ended the class with project progress updates with Alex (hi Alex).
